@startuml stages_opportunity

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
    BorderColor     #555555
    ArrowColor      #333333
    FontSize        12
}

title Opportunity Stage Workflow\n(PATCH /api/opportunities/{id}/stage)

[*] --> PROSPECT : POST /api/opportunities

PROSPECT --> QUALIFY    : advance
PROSPECT --> LOST

QUALIFY --> PROPOSE     : advance
QUALIFY --> LOST

PROPOSE --> NEGOTIATE   : advance
PROPOSE --> LOST

NEGOTIATE --> WON       : advance\n[amount + closeDate required]
NEGOTIATE --> LOST

WON  --> [*]
LOST --> [*]

note right of WON
  **WON gate** — HTTP 400 if either is missing:
    • amount
    • closeDate
end note

note right of QUALIFY
  Every stage transition auto-creates a
  NOTE activity ("Stage changed X → Y by
  <user>") and publishes a StageChangedEvent
  to the opportunity-events RabbitMQ queue.
end note

note bottom of LOST
  Any stage can go directly to LOST.
  Backward transitions rejected (HTTP 400).
end note

@enduml


@startuml stages_project

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
    BorderColor     #555555
    ArrowColor      #333333
    FontSize        12
}

title PMBOK Project Lifecycle\n(POST /api/projects/{id}/…)

' ── Project status ────────────────────────────────────────────
state "Project: **DRAFT**" as PDRAFT
state "Project: **ACTIVE**" as PACTIVE
state "Project: **CLOSED**" as PCLOSED

' ── Charter sub-states ────────────────────────────────────────
state "Charter lifecycle" as charter_group {
    state "Charter: DRAFT"      as CDRAFT
    state "Charter: SUBMITTED"  as CSUBMIT
    state "Charter: APPROVED"   as CAPPROVE
    CDRAFT   --> CSUBMIT  : PM submits\n(/charter/submit)
    CSUBMIT  --> CAPPROVE : SPONSOR approves\n(/charter/approve)
}

' ── Baseline sub-states ───────────────────────────────────────
state "Baseline lifecycle" as baseline_group {
    state "Baseline: DRAFT"     as BDRAFT
    state "Baseline: SUBMITTED" as BSUBMIT
    state "Baseline: APPROVED"  as BAPPROVE
    BDRAFT   --> BSUBMIT  : PM submits\n(/baselines/{v}/submit)
    BSUBMIT  --> BAPPROVE : SPONSOR approves\n(/baselines/{v}/approve)\n[immutable after this]
}

' ── Change Request sub-states ─────────────────────────────────
state "Change Request lifecycle" as cr_group {
    state "CR: DRAFT"       as CRDRAFT
    state "CR: SUBMITTED"   as CRSUBMIT
    state "CR: IN_REVIEW"   as CRREVIEW
    state "CR: APPROVED"    as CRAPPROVE
    state "CR: REJECTED"    as CRREJECT
    state "CR: IMPLEMENTED" as CRIMPLEMENT
    CRDRAFT     --> CRSUBMIT   : member submits
    CRSUBMIT    --> CRREVIEW   : PM reviews
    CRREVIEW    --> CRAPPROVE  : SPONSOR or PM approves\n(SCOPE/SCHEDULE/COST → auto-creates\nnew Baseline DRAFT)
    CRREVIEW    --> CRREJECT   : SPONSOR or PM rejects
    CRAPPROVE   --> CRIMPLEMENT : PM implements\n[linked Baseline must be APPROVED]
}

' ── Closure sub-states ────────────────────────────────────────
state "Closure lifecycle" as closure_group {
    state "Closure: DRAFT"     as CLOSEDRAFT
    state "Closure: SUBMITTED" as CLOSESUBMIT
    state "Closure: APPROVED"  as CLOSEAPPROVE
    CLOSEDRAFT   --> CLOSESUBMIT  : PM submits
    CLOSESUBMIT  --> CLOSEAPPROVE : SPONSOR approves
}

' ── Top-level project flow ────────────────────────────────────
[*]       --> PDRAFT
PDRAFT    --> PACTIVE  : Charter APPROVED
PACTIVE   --> PCLOSED  : POST /close\n[gate: closure APPROVED\n+ all deliverables ACCEPTED]
PCLOSED   --> [*]

note right of PACTIVE
  While ACTIVE:
  • Planning (WBS, tasks, costs, baselines)
  • Execution (deliverables, work logs, issues)
  • Monitoring (CRs, status reports, decisions)
  all run in parallel as needed.
end note

@enduml
